an class=title> Few questions...</span><hr size=1> I have played on the blue servers (karana then Terris) for almost two years now. I have two level 50+ characters and a level 30 all on blue servers. I am becoming very bored with the game <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and want something different. PvP seems the be to be my answer. I am posting here because I have a few questions about PvP. <br>
<br>
1. How does the SK measure up in PvP?<br>
2. If I were to go with the SK should I make a Troll or Iksar for the regen effect? <br>
3. I like the idea of coin + one item like they have on RZ, but I hear RZ is not a fun server to play on and in RZ players own words there are a lot of “weird-o’s who play on RZ. Is this true? <br>
4. What are the best Melee PvP classes for casters and melees?<br>
<br>
Any info would be awesome, thanks for your time!<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif width=0 height=0 border=0 BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/15/00 12:28:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/trinity.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Few questions...</span><hr size=1> Naw, RZ aint full of wierdos. I'm the only one! <mad cackling laugh> Seriously, RZ is the only server I have ever played on, so I really don't know what others are like.<br>
<br>
I will warn you, think of levels 1 - 5 as a test of endurance. You WILL get pk'ed, dozens if not scores of times. Well, maybe not if a troll as there won't be a third as many newbies at the gates as, says, qeynos, but it's going to happen.<br>
<br>
Well anyway try it out I say, get your character to 10 and then dump him if you want.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><a href="maileto:chris.painter@juno.com">Canbik the Rogue</a> (23)<br>
<a href="http://pub21.ezboard.com/bsilentvigilforums">Silent Vigil</a><br>
<a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse">Ring Warden of Rallos Zek</a><br>
"I will make your mother childless..."<br>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uceescrit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ceescrit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/15/00 8:29:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Few questions...</span><hr size=1> At mid levels (20+), a well played SK can be one of THE toughest classes to fight (especially for a rogue).  I pretty much look at them like a warrior with snare, siphon STR (this is bad when this lands), shadowstep and a pet.  Troll SKs are the worst (or best in their case).  Seems like they just have never ending HPs, and hit hard as hell.<br>
<br>
As far as the best class to fight a pure caster.... ROGUES! <p><br><IMG SRC="http://www.aztecmfgcorp.com/_private/sigpic.jpg" height=300 width=490 align=left> <BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>
Ceescrit DaHustla<BR>
Assassin of the 30th season<BR>
Officer, Order of the Black Rose<BR>
a.k.a. Cee Murda of the Faydark</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/15/00 10:07:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Few questions...</span><hr size=1> Rallos is crazy.  You log on in a city like Freeport or Qeynos and there are bodies everywhere.  It's hilarious, and then someone sees you and kills you.  And kills you again.  And again.  Until you move up a bit in levels, 5+, it's pretty much a test to thicken your skin.<br>
<br>
I play mostly on Vallon and prefer the teams setup, although I wish we had item loot back again.  <br>
<br>
Sks are really tough opponents.  Everytime I'm fighting what I think to be a warrior, and he starts to cast, I go, "Oh damn."  They hurt, bad.<br>
<br>
Morvran <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufreonsmurf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FreonSmurf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif  BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/15/00 2:34:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hoels76.tripod.com/wee.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Few questions...</span><hr size=1> If you go SK please go human.<br>
<br>
You can kill halfings, elves and other vermin in Freeport.<br>
You can also kill dark elves as well.<br>
Human SK's are rare on the human/erud/barb team.<br>
<br>
Make it a racewar server and play a non evil team, but still kill the other 3 teams. <p><P><center><font face ="Verdana,Arial" size="3" color="red">
